FBIS3-23110 "jptot010__l94073" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA EGYPT German Tourist on Nile Cruise Shot by Muslim Militants Source Comments, Injured Named NC0403140694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 4 Mar 94 NC0403140694 Cairo MENA Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Asyut, 4 Mar (MENA)--A German woman tourist [as received] was wounded today when unidentified persons opened fire on the cruise boat New Jersey, operated by the Travco Tourist Company, between Asyut and Suhaj Governorates near al-Badari village. The wounded tourist was identified as Isis Gorjess [name as received], 54 years old. She was among a 33-member German tourist group boarding the boat on their way to Cairo from Luxor. The boat sustained slight damage as a result of the shooting. Security forces surrounded the scene of the incident to search for the fugitive assailants. The Al-Badari Prosecution Office has started an investigation. [In a related report, Cairo MENA in Arabic at 1325 adds: "A responsible security source at the Ministry of Interior has stated that at approximately 1000 this morning, unidentified persons opened fire at a boat in the Nile that was carrying a tourist group. The boat was coming from Suhaj and heading toward Asyut. A German woman tourist named Isis Gorjess was wounded by the flying glass resulting from the shooting. She was given first aid and transferred to Asyut University Hospital. Senior officials from the Asyut Security Directorate and various investigating departments moved to the scene of the incident for an examination. The prosecution has been told to open an investigation."]
